 * Is fired everytime mouse click released.  fired even if double (or more) clicks.
 * If a second click is fired within the time set up by the OS allowed for a double click, records 1st click (clickCount = 1)
 * and then records the second click the next time the mouseReleased() is called.
 * Cannot simply use an if(clickCount =1) or clickcount =2 to call different events, especially if they are completely different events
 * as the first time goes into mouseReleased() the if clickcount =1 will be called.
 * 
